# Design System and Brandbook Usage

**IMPORTANT**: When working on frontend components, styles, or UI elements, always reference and use the design system documented in the brandbook.

## Brandbook Location

The design system is documented at:
- **Page**: `src/app/design/page.tsx`
- **URL**: `/design` (when running the app)
- **Test file**: `src/app/design/__tests__/page.test.tsx`

## When to Reference the Brandbook

**ALWAYS** check the brandbook when:
- ✅ Creating new components or UI elements
- ✅ Adding colors, backgrounds, or borders
- ✅ Setting typography (fonts, sizes, weights)
- ✅ Applying spacing (margins, padding, gaps)
- ✅ Using border radius values
- ✅ Creating buttons, inputs, cards, or other UI components
- ✅ Adding status indicators or alerts
- ✅ Working with dark mode styles

## Design System Guidelines

### Colors

**Primary Colors:**
- Use `blue-600` (`#2563eb`) for primary actions and buttons
- Use `blue-500` (`#3b82f6`) for links and focus states
- Use `blue-700` (`#1d4ed8`) for button hover states
- Use `indigo-600` (`#4f46e5`) for gradient accents

**Neutral Colors:**
- Use zinc scale for backgrounds, borders, and text
- `zinc-50` for page backgrounds
- `zinc-100` for disabled states
- `zinc-200` for borders and dividers
- `zinc-400` for placeholder text
- `zinc-600` for secondary text
- `zinc-900` for card backgrounds
- `black` for page background (dark mode)
- `white` for card backgrounds and text (dark mode)

**Status Colors:**
- `green-600` for success states, good deals, high confidence
- `yellow-600` for warnings, medium confidence, replicas
- `red-600` for errors, overpriced items, low confidence
- `purple-100` for feature highlights

**DO NOT** use arbitrary colors. Always use colors from the brandbook palette.

### Typography

- **Font Family**: Use Geist Sans (`font-sans`) for all body text and headings
- **Headings**:
  - H1: `text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight`
  - H2: `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
  - H3: `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
  - H4: `text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- **Body Text**:
  - Large: `text-lg leading-8`
  - Base: `leading-7` (default)
  - Small: `text-sm`
- **Line Heights**: Use `leading-7` for body, `leading-8` for large text
- **Font Weights**: Use `font-semibold` for headings, `font-bold` only for hero text

### Spacing

- Use spacing scale consistently (4px increments)
- Common values: `gap-4`, `gap-6`, `gap-8` for component spacing
- Hero sections: `py-24`
- Standard sections: `py-12`
- Component padding: `p-6` for cards, `px-4 py-2` for buttons

### Border Radius

- Hero inputs: `rounded-2xl`
- Cards: `rounded-2xl`
- Form inputs: `rounded-lg` or `rounded-2xl` (hero)
- Buttons: `rounded-2xl` (hero), `rounded-xl` (standard)
- Small elements: `rounded-lg`

### Components

**Buttons:**
- Primary: `h-14 px-8 text-base font-semibold rounded-2xl bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700`
- Secondary: `px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium rounded-xl border-2 border-zinc-300`
- Outline: `px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium rounded-xl border-2`
- Ghost: `px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-zinc-100 rounded-xl`

**Inputs:**
- Hero style: `h-14 pl-12 pr-4 text-base rounded-2xl border-2 border-zinc-200`
- Standard: `px-4 py-2 border border-zinc-300 rounded-lg`
- Always include focus states: `focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-blue-500/20`

**Cards:**
- Standard: `p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800`
- With shadow: Add `shadow-md` for elevation

**Status Indicators:**
- Success: `bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-800 dark:text-green-200`
- Warning: `bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900/30 text-yellow-800 dark:text-yellow-200`
- Error: `bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 text-red-800 dark:text-red-200`

## Dark Mode

**ALWAYS** include dark mode variants:
- Use `dark:` prefix for dark mode styles
- Test both light and dark modes
- Ensure sufficient contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum)

## Workflow

When creating or modifying frontend components:

1. **Check the brandbook** (`src/app/design/page.tsx`) for:
   - Available colors and their usage
   - Typography scale and classes
   - Spacing conventions
   - Component patterns

2. **Use design tokens** from the brandbook:
   - Don't invent new colors or spacing values
   - Follow existing patterns
   - Maintain consistency with the design system

3. **Reference examples** in the brandbook:
   - Look at component examples
   - Follow the same structure and styling
   - Use the same class names and patterns

4. **Update the brandbook** if adding new:
   - Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
   - Component patterns
   - Usage guidelines

## Examples

### ✅ Good: Using Brandbook Colors

```tsx
// Uses blue-600 from brandbook for primary button
<button className="bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 rounded-2xl">
  Submit
</button>
```

### ❌ Bad: Using Arbitrary Colors

```tsx
// Don't use arbitrary colors not in the brandbook
<button className="bg-[#ff5733] text-white">
  Submit
</button>
```

### ✅ Good: Using Brandbook Typography

```tsx
// Uses H1 typography from brandbook
<h1 className="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
  Title
</h1>
```

### ❌ Bad: Using Arbitrary Typography

```tsx
// Don't use arbitrary font sizes
<h1 className="text-[32px] font-black">
  Title
</h1>
```

### ✅ Good: Using Brandbook Spacing

```tsx
// Uses spacing scale from brandbook
<div className="flex gap-4 p-6">
  <Card />
  <Card />
</div>
```

### ❌ Bad: Using Arbitrary Spacing

```tsx
// Don't use arbitrary spacing values
<div className="flex gap-[13px] p-[23px]">
  <Card />
  <Card />
</div>
```

